OL,3,CThree arrests over 'distressing'
OL,4,Cclaims of grave interference
OL,6,FTwo 25-year-old men and a 53-year-old
OL,7,Fman have been arrested on suspicion of
OL,8,Fconspiracy to commit criminal damage
OL,9,Fand causing a public nuisance.
OL,11,FSouth Yorkshire Police said relatives
OL,12,Fof the dead person were being
OL,13,Fsupported by specialist officers.
OL,15,FDet Insp Lucy Garside said: "This
OL,16,Fwould have been an extremely
OL,17,Fdistressing and concerning time for
OL,18,Fthose who have loved ones also in the
OL,19,Fchurch yard.
